### 7. üìä How to Get Vote Data (Suara)

The vote results system works via the existing backend API:

#### API Endpoints
| Method | Endpoint | Purpose |
|--------|----------|---------|
| `GET` | `/api/vote-results` | List all vote results (paginated) |
| `GET` | `/api/vote-results?aggregate=true` | Aggregated per-district summary |
| `POST` | `/api/vote-results` | Submit new vote result |
| `PUT` | `/api/vote-results/{id}` | Update vote result |
| `GET` | `/api/vote-results/{id}` | Show single result |

#### Submitting Vote Data
To input vote results, send a `POST` to `/api/vote-results` with:
```json
{
  "polling_station_id": 1,
  "party_votes": 150,
  "total_votes": 500,
  "dpt": 800,
  "voters_present": 520,
  "verified": false
}
```

The `submitted_by` and `submitted_at` are automatically set by the backend from the authenticated user.

#### Data Flow
```mermaid
graph LR
    A["Officer at TPS"] -->|"Input results"| B["POST /vote-results"]
    B --> C["Database"]
    C -->|"GET ?aggregate=true"| D["Aggregated View"]
    C -->|"GET (paginated)"| E["Detailed View"]
    D --> F["Bar Chart + District Table"]
    E --> G["Per-TPS Table"]
```

> [!TIP]
> The Vote Results page already has both **Aggregated View** (charts + district summary) and **Detailed View** (per-TPS table). Officers can input data via `POST /api/vote-results` from a mobile app or the dashboard form.

